description.plain:
Dexter Tiewon Gore Jr. (b. September 6, 1993), better known as his stage name Famous Dex (formerly Black Migo Dex), is a rapper from Chicago, Illinois. He was born in Englewood.

He went to Robeson High School, the same school as fellow Chicago rapper Lil Durk. He is also the cousin of another fellow Chicago rapper, Lil Wop.

On March 6th, 2016, Famous Dex was announced as the first signee to Rich The Kid’s label Rich Forever Music.

songs.title: PICK IT UP

description.plain:
“Pick It Up” is accompanied with a feature from A$AP Rocky and marks their second collaboration since A$AP Ferg’s “The Mattress" (Remix).

In this song, both Dexter and Flacko flaunt their wealth and reminisce about old times.

With the praised production by FKi 1st and Sosa 808, the banger quickly gained traction accumulating 1.5 million views in just a week on the WSHH exclusive video.



The official music video, directed by AWGE/ Hidji Films was released on January 17, 2018.

songs.full_title: JAPAN by Famous Dex
songs.title: JAPAN

description.plain:
“Japan” is the second single from Famous Dex’s debut album, Dex Meets Dexter. It has reached a peak of #28 on the Billboard Hot 100.

Originally previewed in the album trailer, the J Gramm-produced song was finally released on March 16th, 2018.

The song began to gain traction after Roy Purdy posted a video dancing to it, sparking a new trend called the #JapanChallenge:

https://www.instagram.com/p/BgpB1mhgorx/?hl=en&taken-by=roypurdy

Dex is well-acquainted with Purdy, being spotted in photos together (Dex himself has also attempted the #JapanChallenge, paying homage to Purdy in the caption), and embraced the trend by reposting a video of LeBron James Jr. doing the #JapanChallenge.

songs.full_title: Hoes Mad by Famous Dex
songs.title: Hoes Mad

description.plain:
On “Hoes Mad,” Dexter details his disdain towards women who expect him to be committed to a relationship.

Despite releasing in August of 2015, “Hoes Mad” resurged in popularity in April 2019, becoming a popular reaction meme across social media.
